	   <tr><td colspan=2>Stoutoak asked, &quot;what is a chanter mezzing at this level??&quot;<br><br>The mobs in Vex Thal often spawn in groups that are hard or slow to split. A pull to the raid may bring 6 mobs. Some of them typically can be mezzed, while some cannot. The main tank chooses an unmezzable mob and most everyone assists the main tank to kill it. Other tanks attack the other unmezzable mobs (&quot;add tanking&quot; or &quot;tank mezzing&quot;). The chanters must mez the remaining mobs until all the other mobs are killed.<br><br>Also, in the Ssraeshza Temple Emperor encounter, the trigger mob (Blood) is surrounded by tough guards. It is useless to kill these mobs because they are insta-respawn. Chanters must mez some of these mobs throughout the duration of the encounter, which may take 25 minutes (and the other guards must be tank mezzed). It does help that bards sing mana song throughout the fight, that nerfed mod rods are available, and necros are standing by to twitch people who need mana.<br><br>The critical mana drain on the Emperor and many other big fights is cleric mana.<br><br>This Belt of Dark Thoughts dropped last night. A paladin went for it. I (cleric) did, too. We both had about the same rpp (raid participation points), so it looked like a rolloff. Then the paladin graciously withdrew, pointing out that cleric FT4 &gt; paladin FT4.<br>&nbsp;<br>Forthoffer, 65/92 cleric, The Shadow Order, Lanys T'Vyl</td></tr>
